{
NPCText "[Dr. Oswald said, \"if a terminally ill patient were to die tomorrow, there would be nothing tying the relatives to Sandover and they could leave whenever they wished. However, if those relatives were to stay in Sandover, would they be in the same shape in twelve months' time?\"]"
      options {
          int=4 linkflags skill_check Reaction=REACTION_GOOD playertext "[Repeat this to Catherine; emphasize the ties that bond people to terminally ill family members.]" linkto "Pro_Euth_Speech_4b"  notes "Normal Speech skill check.\nCatherine implied in earlier dialogue how she disliked the responsibilites that came with her family life. This option is a nice way to play on that.\nNote: for the Speech check, add/subtract the local variable Cath_Mood to the difficulty modifier."
          int=4 linkflags skill_check Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[Repeat this to Catherine; emphasize the vicious circle effect of Sandover's radiation on terminal patients' relatives.]" linkto "Pro_Euth_Speech_4a"  notes "Slightly harder Speech skill check.\nAgain with the Sandover-is-a-dump line! She doesn't like that.\nNote: for the Speech check, add/subtract the local variable Cath_Mood to the difficulty modifier."
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Perhaps I'd better ask you about something else." linkto "Cath_9"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Never mind. Goodbye." linkto "done"  notes ""
              }
}
