{
NPCText "[David said, \"a lot of people think that there are only two alternatives open to patients with a terminal illness. On the one hand, they die slowly in painful, unrelieved suffering; on the other hand, they receive euthanasia. There is, however, a third way - compassionate medical care. You can use drugs to alleviate the pain of, if not to cure, a terminal illness.\"]"
      options {
          int=4 linkflags skill_check Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[Put the same argument to Catherine; emphasize that drugs exist which can ease the suffering of terminally ill people.]" linkto "Anti_Euth_Speech_1a"  notes "Slightly harder Speech skill check.\nCatherine revealed earlier that she uses anti-rad drugs herself. She won't like to be reminded that these could be used on people much worse off than she is.\nNote: for the Speech check, add/subtract the local variable Cath_Mood to the difficulty modifier."
          int=4 linkflags skill_check Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[Put the same argument to Catherine; emphasize the difference between compassion and killing in medicine.]" linkto "Anti_Euth_Speech_1b"  notes "Normal Speech skill check.\nCatherine revealed earlier that she played a part in making sure that the Vultures weren't killed when they were thrown out of the caves. This showed that she can put the sanctity of life above practicality.\nNote: for the Speech check, add/subtract the local variable Cath_Mood to the difficulty modifier."
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Perhaps I'd better ask you about something else." linkto "Cath_9"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Never mind. Goodbye." linkto "done"  notes ""
              }
}
