{
NPCText "[David said, \"If we ask our doctors to kill their own patients, that's going to put them off learning medicine in the first place. Who actually wants that kind of ethical burden? Mark my words: if you legalize euthanasia, you say goodbye to dedicated health-workers.\"]"
      options {
          int=4 linkflags skill_check Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[Repeat this to Catherine; emphasize the extra ethical burden euthanasia puts upon health workers.]" linkto "Anti_Euth_Speech_2a"  notes "Normal Speech skill check.\nCatherine revealed earlier that she resents the burden of responsibility put upon her being Sandover's leader's daughter. This will help her empathise with other people's ethical load.\nNote: for the Speech check, add/subtract the local variable Cath_Mood to the difficulty modifier."
          int=4 linkflags skill_check Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[Repeat this to Catherine; emphasize the risk that Sandover could stand to lose some of its health workers.]" linkto "Anti_Euth_Speech_2b"  notes "Slightly harder Speech skill check.\nSandover could lose some of its health workers? It's not like anyone is in the caves by choice. Even morally difficult health work is better than being a scavenger.\nNote: for the Speech check, add/subtract the local variable Cath_Mood to the difficulty modifier."
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Perhaps I'd better ask you about something else." linkto "Cath_9"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Never mind. Goodbye." linkto "done"  notes ""
              }
}
