{
NPCText "[David said, \"When considerate people are dying, the last thing they want is to be a burden to anybody. Some very ill people feel that assisted suicide is something they ought to request, as a matter of duty, for the sake of their families and the overstretched healthcare facilities in Sandover.\"]"
      options {
          int=4 linkflags skill_check Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[Repeat this to Catherine; emphasize the risk that a sick Scab could request euthanasia to avoid being a burden to his family.]" linkto "Anti_Euth_Speech_3a"  notes "Slightly harder Speech skill check.\nAgain, this plays on Catherine's resentment of her family duties/burdens. She sees herself as someone who is put upon by others, not the other way around. She does not empathise with the self-sacrifice mentality.\nNote: for the Speech check, add/subtract the local variable Cath_Mood to the difficulty modifier."
          int=4 linkflags skill_check Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[Repeat this to Catherine; emphasize the risk that a sick Scab could request euthanasia to avoid putting extra strain on Sandover's healthcare resources.]" linkto "Anti_Euth_Speech_3b"  notes "Normal Speech skill check.\nNo personal bias as far as Catherine is concerned.\nNote: for the Speech check, add/subtract the local variable Cath_Mood to the difficulty modifier."
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Perhaps I'd better ask you about something else." linkto "Cath_9"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Never mind. Goodbye." linkto "done"  notes ""
              }
}
